<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-577-008  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 577 008.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Federal Computer Week  June 18 1990 v4 n24 p1(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>DOD slashes ADP budget to finance CIM program. (Department ofDefense; Corporate Information Management initiative)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Marsan, Carolyn Duffy; Brewin, Bob.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The US Department of Defense will decrease all services' ADPbudgets to discourage new system development in areas that willcompete with similar areas falling under the Corporate InformationManagement initiative.andP;  Approximately $1.2 billion will beeliminated in order to develop tri-service ADP systems, ratherthan service-unique systems as has been done in the past.andP;  Areasincluded for cutting include civilian personnel, civilian payroll,financial management, supply management, warehousing, contractmanagement, medical services and contract payments.andP;  Hardest hitwill be the Naval Supply Systems Command, the Army MaterielCommand and the Air Force Logistics Command.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Government FundingBudgetingGovernment RegulationProduct DevelopmentUnited States. Department of Defense.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>